const headHtml = "<title>Bazaar Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</title>\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"An expert based 2026 bazaar flipping guide for Hypixel SkyBlock covering buy orders, sell offers, spread discipline, market depth, passive fills and the tools that expose real liquidity.\">\n    <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/bazaar-flipping-guide-2026\">\n\n    <meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/bazaar-flipping-guide-2026\">\n    <meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\">\n    <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Bazaar Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026\">\n    <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Use the bazaar like a real order book: work the spread, respect volume, and stop confusing a big screenshot margin with a usable flip.\">\n    <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/static/NEC.png\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\n        \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n        \"@type\": \"BlogPosting\",\n        \"headline\": \"Bazaar Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026\",\n        \"description\": \"Expert based guide to buy-order and sell-offer bazaar flipping in Hypixel SkyBlock.\",\n        \"datePublished\": \"2026-01-12\",\n        \"dateModified\": \"2026-04-18\",\n        \"author\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n          \"name\": \"NotEnoughCoins\"\n        },\n        \"publisher\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n          \"name\": \"Coflnet GmbH\"\n        },\n        \"url\": \"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/bazaar-flipping-guide-2026\"\n      }\n    </script>";
const bodyHtml = "<main>\n      <div class=\"site-shell article-layout\">\n        <article class=\"article\">\n          <a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-01-12 • Bazaar Flipping</a>\n          <h1>Bazaar Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</h1>\n          <p class=\"lede\">Bazaar flipping stays profitable because the core business never changed: place disciplined buy orders, exit through sell offers, and only touch markets where the spread is backed by real volume. The mistake most players make is treating the bazaar like a list of magical items instead of an order book. Once you start reading fill speed, demand and exit depth together, the method becomes much easier to scale.</p>\n\n          <div class=\"note\">\n            <strong>Primary source base:</strong> Xentyl's 2026 bazaar guide plus Kuvdra's wider bazaar walkthrough covering active flips, passive orders, book crafts and event-driven demand.\n          </div>\n\n          <h2>Advanced mode is not optional</h2>\n          <p>If you want better bazaar decisions, turn on the information the default interface hides. Recent insta-buy and insta-sell data matters because it tells you whether a spread belongs to an active market or to an item with almost no real movement. A wide spread on a dead product is not a beginner flip. It is a waiting room with better marketing.</p>\n          <p>This is also why the strongest creator advice keeps sounding boring. High-volume items with stable order flow are rarely flashy, but they let you recycle capital. In practice, that makes them better than dramatic percentage spreads on niche products that only trade in tiny bursts.</p>\n\n          <h2>The spread is the job</h2>\n          <p>Every good bazaar flip is a timing trade between two prices. You buy with patience and you sell with patience. The moment you start instant buying or instant selling out of frustration, you hand the edge to the players who kept their discipline. That is why the real skill is not finding the item name. It is finding a spread that survives fees, competition and the time it takes to get filled.</p>\n          <p>Liquidity changes what a good flip looks like. A thin item with a giant margin can still be worse than a resource with a tiny spread if the resource cycles quickly enough. Coins per hour, fill certainty and repeatability beat screenshot-worthy gaps almost every time.</p>\n\n          <h2>Decide whether you want active or passive bazaar play</h2>\n          <p>Active bazaar flipping is closer to manual trading. You watch the spread, tweak orders and think about short-term demand. Passive bazaar play is different. It is built around liquid items, calm order placement and letting fills accumulate in the background while you do other content. Both work, but they should not be judged by the same expectations.</p>\n          <p>If you keep mixing the two mindsets, you end up sabotaging both. Passive orders feel too slow, active flips feel too noisy, and neither gets a fair chance to work. Pick the routine that matches how you actually play.</p>\n\n          <h2>Use live depth and demand tools</h2>\n          <p>Live dashboards are especially useful on the bazaar because they compress three checks at once: spread size, demand and order-book depth. <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bazaar\">SkyCofl bazaar</a> surfaces live prices quickly, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/premiumBazaar\">premium bazaar</a> adds deeper order-flow context, <a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/bazaar-flipping\">BazaarPro bazaar flipping</a> layers on rule-based workflows, <a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/flips\">Skyblock.bz flips</a> helps compare opportunities by ROI, and <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/smart\">BazaarTracker smart</a>, <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/margin\">margin</a> and <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/demand\">demand</a> give a fast second opinion. Use the overlap between tools to confirm that the spread is real.</p>\n\n          <h2>Read next</h2>\n          <ul class=\"related-list\">\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/passive-bazaar-orders-guide\">Passive Bazaar Orders Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/craft-flipping-guide-2026\">Craft Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/npc-to-bazaar-flips\">NPC to Bazaar Flips in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n\n        <aside class=\"article-aside\">\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best paired tools</h3>\n            <ul class=\"tool-list\">\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bazaar\">SkyCofl bazaar</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/premiumBazaar\">SkyCofl premium bazaar</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/subscriptions\">SkyCofl notifiers</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/bazaar-flipping\">BazaarPro bazaar flipping</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/flips\">Skyblock.bz flips</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/smart\">BazaarTracker smart</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/margin\">BazaarTracker margin</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/demand\">BazaarTracker demand</a></li>\n            </ul>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best for</h3>\n            <p>Players who want repeatable market income and are willing to trade a little excitement for clearer, more scalable execution.</p>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Source videos</h3>\n            <p>Xentyl and Kuvdra are the strongest references here because they emphasize spread quality and market depth instead of one-off item calls.</p>\n          </div>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n    </main>";
